Architecture Design and Setup

Components:
Data Ingestion
Data Storage
Data Processing
Data Aggregation
Data Visualization

Detailed Breakdown:
Data Ingestion:

AWS S3: Store raw data files.
AWS Kinesis Firehose: Stream real-time data.
AWS Data Pipeline: Orchestrate batch data ingestion.

Data Storage:

AWS S3: For raw and processed data.
AWS Redshift: For structured and semi-structured data.
AWS RDS (PostgreSQL): For transactional data.

Data Processing:

AWS Glue: Serverless ETL service.
AWS EMR: For large-scale data processing using Apache Spark/Hadoop.
AWS Lambda: For real-time processing and simple transformations.

Data Aggregation:

AWS Athena: Query data directly from S3 using SQL.
AWS Redshift Spectrum: Query data in S3 without moving it to Redshift.

Data Visualization:

AWS QuickSight: Business intelligence service for creating dashboards.
Tableau/Power BI: For advanced visualization needs.
